                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1399</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-05T15:00:00-04:49">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 5, 1916, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My May 31, ten a.m. and June 1, eleven a.m. At one o’clock yesterday morning Caco
                    chiefs Codio and Metellus and band were surrounded near Fonds Verretes and in
                    desperate effort to escape Codio, Metellus and nine others were shot. The
                    American forces and gendarmes are in pursuit of the other outlaws. Reports show
                    all quiet in the provinces.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
